COMPONENT NAME: LKM DB2/400 Journal to SQL COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.2 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 10.1.3.5.0 and above
Knowledge Loading Module Loads data from an DB2/400 database to any ISO-92 compliant target database.
This module uses ODI Agent to read selected data from the database and write the result in the target temporary table created dynamically.
When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
This special LKM also executes the CDCRTVJRN program to retrieve Journal entries into the J$ table if required. Please read the Options descriptions carefully. Note : that the step calling the CDCRTVJRN could be executed within package outside of this LKM
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module is NOT RECOMMENDED when using LARGE VOLUMES.
Uncheck thit option if you want to keep the work table after integration

Retrive native journal entries. This option causes the LKM to run the CDCRTVJRN stored procedure that connects to the native iSeries journal. You have to set the SUBSCRIBER_NAME option when using this option

Check this option if you want to create a spool file on the iSeries. A spool file is usefull for debugging in case of problem when running the Retrieve Journal Entries stored procedure. To access to this spool file: - Connect to your iSeries using the same login as the one used for the DB2/400 DataServer user name in Sunopsis Topology - Issue the command WRKSPLF and edit the last CDCRTVJRN spool file
Set this option to the Subscriber Name when using the RETRIEVE_JOURNAL_ENTRIES feature

update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L", "SUBSCRIBER_TABLE", "A" )%> set JRN_ROW_COUNT = JRN_ROW_COUNT - (select count(*) from <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> ) where JRN_TNAME = '<%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' and JRN_SUBSCRIBER = '<%=snpRef.getOption("SUBSCRIBER_NAME")%>'
